The increase in production in the eurozone slowed to the lowest point in the last 13 months in August, according to a closely monitored study.
The final Markit Purchasing Manager Index of Manufacturing (PMI) fell to 50.7 in August, down from 51.8 in July.
An indication over 50 indicates an expansion.
New orders fell and factories experienced breakdowns at a time of rising tensions between the EU and Russia over Ukraine.
The figures arrive before the European Central Bank (ECB) meeting on Thursday.
