Meanwhile, the PMI fell to 46.9 in the block’s second largest economic nation, France.
France remains a child of worries, as is the decline of Italy from a solid expansion to stagnation.
Evidence that growth incentives in Germany's key industrial mechanism, as well as in Spain and the Netherlands, are also not reassuring," Mr Dobson said.
